messages.content: What is ComfyUI_Native_DynamiCrafter?
ComfyUI_Native_DynamiCrafter is a DynamiCrafter that works natively with ComfyUI's nodes, optimizations, ControlNet, and more.
What is required to get ComfyUI_Native_DynamiCrafter installed?
Go to your `custom_nodes` directory in ComfyUI, and install by `git clone https://github.com/ExponentialML/ComfyUI_Native_DynamiCrafter.git`.
Where can the last stable branch can be found?
[here](https://github.com/ExponentialML/ComfyUI_Native_DynamiCrafter/tree/43ae6bebccb141c6d85b5075f4fed57a5ddea3c1)
What models are used with ComfyUI_Native_DynamiCrafter?
A VAE, The CLIP model used with Stable Diffusion 2.1, and the Open CLIP Vision Model.
Where are the DynamiCrafter models placed?
DynamiCrafter models are placed inside `ComfyUI_Path/models/dynamicrafter_models`.
What is the use of `use_interpolation` in ComfyUI_Native_DynamiCrafter?
Use the interpolation mode with the interpolation model variant. You can interpolate any two frames (images), or predict the rest using one input.
What is the range of values for `fps` in ComfyUI_Native_DynamiCrafter?
If you're using a 256 based model, the highest plausible value is **4**.
What is the maximum value for `frames` in ComfyUI_Native_DynamiCrafter?
The max is **16**.
Can ControlNet be used with ComfyUI_Native_DynamiCrafter?
Yes, ControlNet can be used with ComfyUI_Native_DynamiCrafter by applying it to the Spatial (image) portion to guide video generations in various ways.
Can you use your own latents with ComfyUI_Native_DynamiCrafter?
Yes, as long as you use the same frame length (as your batch size) and same height and width as your image inputs, you can use your own latents.
What are the future plans for ComfyUI_Native_DynamiCrafter?
Add advanced workflows, autoregressive nodes, and ensure attention optimizations are working properly.
